3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"KuCoin calculates BLUR/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The funding rate is capped at ±0.75% per interval to prevent extreme payouts. Long positions pay shorts when rates are positive, reflecting bullish sentiment typically seen during NFT market cycles. KuCoin's funding rate formula incorporates both premium and interest rate components, with the interest rate set at 0.01% for USDT-margined contracts."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BLUR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's connection to the NFT marketplace ecosystem creates unique funding rate patterns tied to broader NFT market sentiment and Ethereum network activity. The token's relatively small market cap compared to major cryptocurrencies can result in higher volatility and more pronounced funding rate swings. KuCoin's altcoin-friendly platform provides better BLUR perpetual liquidity than many larger exchanges that focus primarily on major cryptocurrencies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR/USDT funding rates on KuCoin have shown correlation with NFT market cycles and Ethereum gas fee fluctuations. During periods of high NFT trading activity, funding rates often turn positive as traders take leveraged long positions expecting increased BLUR utility demand. The 8-hour settlement frequency allows for more responsive rate adjustments compared to daily funding systems. Rates typically range from -0.3% to +0.4% per interval, with extreme readings during major NFT market events or BLUR protocol updates reaching the ±0.75% caps."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR/USDT funding rate arbitrage works best during periods of divergent sentiment between spot NFT markets and perpetual futures positioning. Traders can capture funding payments by taking opposite positions when rates exceed typical ranges, particularly effective given BLUR's smaller market cap creating more pronounced rate movements. The key opportunity window occurs during NFT market volatility when spot demand doesn't align with futures positioning. KuCoin's competitive maker fees of 0.02% help preserve arbitrage margins, though position sizing should account for the pair's moderate liquidity constraints."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR/USDT perpetual trading on KuCoin carries elevated risks due to the token's connection to NFT market cycles and relatively thin liquidity compared to major pairs. Sudden shifts in NFT sentiment can cause rapid funding rate changes and significant price gaps that may trigger liquidations. KuCoin's regulatory challenges following 2023 SEC charges add counterparty risk considerations for funding rate strategies. The exchange's moderate perpetual liquidity means larger positions may face slippage issues, and funding rate arbitrage should be sized appropriately to avoid market impact during volatile NFT market periods."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are BLUR/USDT funding rates calculated on KuCoin?","answer":"KuCoin calculates and settles BLUR/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. This tri-daily settlement allows for more responsive rate adjustments compared to daily funding systems, particularly important for volatile altcoin pairs like BLUR."},{"question":"What's the maximum funding rate for BLUR/USDT on KuCoin?","answer":"KuCoin caps funding rates at ±0.75% per 8-hour interval for BLUR/USDT perpetuals. This translates to a maximum theoretical daily rate of ±2.25%, though such extreme levels are rare and typically occur only during major market events or protocol updates affecting the BLUR ecosystem."},{"question":"How does BLUR's NFT marketplace connection affect funding rates?","answer":"BLUR funding rates often correlate with NFT market activity and Ethereum network congestion since BLUR operates as an NFT marketplace token. During high-volume NFT trading periods, funding rates frequently turn positive as traders anticipate increased BLUR utility demand, creating arbitrage opportunities when spot and futures sentiment diverge."},{"question":"What are the main liquidity constraints for BLUR/USDT funding arbitrage on KuCoin?","answer":"BLUR/USDT has moderate liquidity on KuCoin compared to major pairs, meaning position sizes should be limited to avoid market impact. The pair typically maintains sufficient depth for smaller arbitrage positions, but large funding rate strategies may face slippage issues, particularly during volatile NFT market periods when spreads can widen significantly."}]}]
